## 9. Customer order-status link format

When sending shipment notification emails, link customers to the client site's
order-lookup page:

```
{client.domain}{client.order_lookup_path}?order_number={pi.id}&order_email={encodeURIComponent(customerEmail)}
```

Example:
`https://www.cabfreshfiltercompany.com/orders/lookup?order_number=pi_3Pxyz...&order_email=customer%40example.com`

The client site reads `order_number` and `order_email`, prefills the form,
and auto-submits. This is the canonical template — all Stripe sites must
implement the same lookup page behavior.

---

## 10. Dashboard order detail link (for business notification emails)

```
{requestOrigin(req)}/orders/{pi.id}
```

Use `requestOrigin` from `lib/url.ts` to derive the dashboard origin from
request headers. Do not hardcode the dashboard URL.

---

## 11. Edit reconciliation (succeeded PI)

A `succeeded` PI's captured amount cannot be increased in place:

- **New total LOWER**: issue a partial refund via `refunds.create({ payment_intent, amount: diff })`.
- **New total HIGHER**: create a Stripe Invoice for the delta, finalize and send it. Record the Invoice ID in `metadata.outstanding_invoice`.

Always keep `metadata.lines`, `metadata.subtotal`, and `metadata.shipping`
consistent with the intended order contents (not necessarily with the net-charged
amount after partial refunds).

On the first edit that changes `lines`, freeze the prior values into
`original_lines` / `original_subtotal` and set `edited_at`. Do not overwrite
those keys on later edits. Edit refunds should include refund metadata
`reason: "order_edit"` plus `lines_before` / `lines_after` when possible.

---

## 12. Stripe gates — never skip

Before any order read/write, verify:

```ts
const catalog = await getActiveCatalogProvider()  // must be "stripe"
const keys = await getStripeKeys()                 // must be non-null
```

Use `isStripeOrdersEnabled()` from `lib/stripe/config.ts` for a single-call
convenience check. Redirect to `/dashboard` in pages; return 503 in API routes.
